  "prompt": "Is buying cannon 1200D a good idea for beginner in 2016 or should I go for 1300D?",
  "response": "In 2016, both the Canon EOS 1200D (also known as Rebel T5) and the Canon EOS 1300D (also known as Rebel T6) are suitable choices for beginners. However, the 1300D has a few upgraded features that might be worth considering.\n\nHere are some key differences:\n\n1. **Wi-Fi and NFC:** The Canon 1300D includes built-in Wi-Fi and NFC (Near Field Communication), which allows for easier sharing of photos and remote control via a smartphone. The 1200D does not have these features.\n\n2. **Processor:** The Canon 1300D has a slightly improved DIGIC 4+ processor compared to the DIGIC 4 processor in the 1200D. This offers better image processing and faster performance.\n\n3. **Screen Resolution:** The screen resolution is improved on the 1300D. It has a 920k-dot LCD monitor compared to the 460k-dot monitor on the 1200D. This means the 1300D will display images more clearly and sharply.\n\n4. **Price:** Since both models are entry-level cameras, the price difference might not be substantial, but this could be a factor depending on your budget.\n\nUltimately, the Canon 1300D offers some improvements that could be beneficial for a beginner, especially the connectivity features and better screen resolution. If these features are important to you and fit within your budget, the 1300D may be the better choice. However, if you're looking for a more budget-friendly option and can forego the additional features, the 1200D is still a solid entry-level DSLR.",
